        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 2:44PM MDT by NWS Missoula MT</headline>
        <description>At 244 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Conner, or 21 miles south of Hamilton, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half-inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Conner and Sula.

This includes Highway 93 S between mile markers 12 and 26.
</description>
        <instruction>This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
